data.event: Riverbanks welcomes three black- necked swan cygnets . The cygnets only spent about a day in the nest.
By Saturday they ventured into the water with their parents in search of food.
The male, 9, came to Riverbanks in 2000 from the Santa Ana Zoo and the female, 5, came in 2004 from the Alexandria Zoo.
